React needs a root container to control the UI
Learnt react via CDN 
What is CDN ? Content Delivery Network
A CDN is a network of servers distributed across the world that deliver files (like JS, CSS, images) quickly to users based on their location.
inculded cdn links into my basic html:5 code inorder to have a smooth renderings and rerenderings effectively 
Learnt about ReactDOM.createRoot() which is a  DOM element where you are allowed to control the UI.
How does it work internally : 
                            Finds the real DOM element (<div id="root">)
                            Creates a React root container
                            Enables React’s new concurrent rendering features
Normal DOM update:
Change → Browser re-renders large part → Slower
React way:
Change → Compare → Update only what changed → Faster
Reconciliation in React process by which React updates the real DOM efficiently when the state or props change.
As updating the real DOM is slow we use Recnciliation inorder to make it faster 
creates a new Virtual DOM
Compares it with the previous Virtual DOM
Finds differences
Updates only the changed parts in the real DOM
This comparison process is called  Diffing Algorithm
Understood how rerendering works in event handling 
Learnt overall process of rerendering works and how real dom and virtual dom works 


